## Model Inheritance Patterns

### Extension (`_inherit` only)

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Extend existing model
class ResPartnerPlastOS(models.Model):
    _inherit = "res.partner"
    
    intake_count = fields.Integer(compute="_compute_intake_count")
```

### Delegation (`_inherits`)

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Composition via delegation
class ProductTemplate(models.Model):
    _name = "product.template"
    _inherits = {"product.product": "product_id"}
```

### New Model (`_name` + `_description`)

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — New model with proper metadata
class PlasticosIntake(models.Model):
    _name = "plasticos.intake"
    _description = "Material Intake"
    _order = "create_date desc"
```

