## Search & Browse (Use Domains, Not SQL)

### Domain Syntax

```python
# ❌ WRONG — Raw SQL
self.env.cr.execute("SELECT id FROM res_partner WHERE supplier_rank > 0")

# ✅ CORRECT — Domain search
suppliers = self.env["res.partner"].search([("supplier_rank", ">", 0)])
```

### Complex Domains

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — OR conditions with pipe
domain = [
    "|",
    ("supplier_profile_id", "in", profile_ids),
    ("buyer_profile_id", "in", profile_ids),
]
```

### Search with Limit

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Efficient single-record lookup
partner = self.env["res.partner"].search([("email", "=", email)], limit=1)
```

---

## CRUD Operations

### Create

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Dict-based create
intake = self.env["plasticos.intake"].create({
    "partner_id": partner.id,
    "status": "draft",
})
```

### Write

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Recordset write
self.write({"status": "active"})

# ✅ CORRECT — Direct assignment (single field)
self.status = "active"
```

### Unlink

```python
# ✅ CORRECT — Recordset unlink
obsolete_records.unlink()
```

